            <section id="anglr-language-syntax">
                <h1>Anglr Language Syntax Rules</h1>
                <hr />
                <h4>Introduction</h4>
                <p>
                    This paragraph contains complete set of syntax rules for Anglr Language using nested rules. This is an attractive example, which presents, 
                    how to construct the whole grammar of some programming language using only nested rules. The only standalone rule is starting rule &lt;anglr source&gt;
                    This grammar is equivalent to grammar composed with standalone syntax rules, since they derive the same languages.
                </p>
